Subject: [control-bot] Disable partial-message streaming (fixes dropped parallel subagents)

claude-code-telegram v1.6.0 sets `include_partial_messages=stream_callback is not None`
when building ClaudeAgentOptions, and it always supplies a stream callback (to drive the
Telegram progress bar) — so every run enables token-level partial-message streaming.

With `include_partial_messages=True`, Claude Code (the bundled CLI) treats long-running
parallel `Task` subagents as "deferred tools": while they run, the parent stream is
auto-resumed with an injected "Continue from where you left off." (isMeta) on an
`interrupted_turn`, the subagents' results come back "[Tool result missing due to internal
error]", the model replies "No response requested." and the query ends via `stop_sequence`.
Net effect on /process-voice: the Stage-5 extract subagents are torn down mid-flight, only
the 1–2 candidates already written to disk survive, and the run never reaches Stage-6 merge
(meta.json finished_at stays null). The same skill via the interactive `claude` CLI — which
does not use partial-message streaming — runs to completion.

Proven by an A/B repro (3 parallel Task agents each `sleep 95` then write a file), run
against this exact SDK/CLI in the container:
  include_partial_messages=True  -> FAIL: 0 files, subagents dropped
  include_partial_messages=False -> PASS: all 3 files written
Only that one option differed.

This patch forces `include_partial_messages=False`. The stream callback still receives
*full* message events (SystemMessage/AssistantMessage), so the progress bar keeps updating
at message granularity; only token-level partial deltas are disabled.

Apply during the Phase-7 image build, at the site-packages root (AFTER 0003):
  patch -p1 --forward -d "$SITE" < control-bot/patches/0004-disable-partial-message-streaming.patch
Verify:
  grep -q "control-bot patch 0004" "$SITE/src/claude/sdk_integration.py"
and a real /process-voice run through the bot completes extract -> merge -> summarize ->
finish with meta.json finished_at set.

Generated 2026-07-13 against the installed claude-code-telegram@v1.6.0 source tree
(context above patch 0003's hunk, so it applies cleanly at -p1 in Dockerfile order).

--- a/src/claude/sdk_integration.py
+++ b/src/claude/sdk_integration.py
@@ -327,7 +327,13 @@
                 allowed_tools=sdk_allowed_tools,
                 disallowed_tools=sdk_disallowed_tools,
                 cli_path=self.config.claude_cli_path or None,
-                include_partial_messages=stream_callback is not None,
+                # control-bot patch 0004: force OFF. include_partial_messages=True makes
+                # Claude Code defer and DROP long-running parallel Task subagents mid-run
+                # (A/B repro: slow parallel Tasks PASS with False, FAIL with True), so
+                # /process-voice loses its extract subagents before merge. Full-message
+                # stream events (which drive the progress bar) are still delivered when
+                # this is False; only token-level partial deltas are disabled.
+                include_partial_messages=False,
                 sandbox={
                     "enabled": self.config.sandbox_enabled,
                     "autoAllowBashIfSandboxed": True,
